{% from "govuk/components/warning-text/macro.njk" import govukWarningText %}

<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Barcode already scanned: carry out further checks</h1>
<p>
  Someone scanned this barcode at <strong data-qa='original-scan'>{{ form.errorCode.scannedDate | formatDateTimeForResultsPage }} at {{ form.errorCode.scannedLocation }}</strong>.
  It may be an illegal copy.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How to investigate</h2>
<p>Follow your usual procedures, for example:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>confirm the mail is addressed to <strong data-qa='barcode-recipient'>{{ form.errorCode.recipientName }}, {{ form.errorCode.recipientPrisonNumber if form.errorCode.recipientPrisonNumber else form.errorCode.recipientDob }}</strong></li>
    <li>confirm the sender, <strong data-qa='barcode-created-by'>{{ form.errorCode.createdBy }}</strong>, has a record of sending this item</li>
    <li>check the item has not been tampered with</li>
    <li>make sure there are no drugs or other contraband concealed in the item</li>
</ul>

<p>If you still have concerns, report them to a security manager.</p>
{{ govukWarningText({
  text: 'Do not open any item of Rule 39 mail without permission from a governor and the recipient being present.'
}) }}
